================================================================
PRACTICAL 7(c) - Mouse Activities and Type Into / Type Secure Text
================================================================

DIFFICULTY: Easy

WHAT YOU WILL DO:
You will simulate Mouse Click, Double Click, Hover, Type Into, 
and Type Secure Text using Notepad and Calculator.

--- STEP-BY-STEP INSTRUCTIONS ---

PART 1 - MOUSE CLICK, DOUBLE CLICK, HOVER

Step 1: Open Notepad on your computer.

Step 2: Open UiPath Studio → New Project.
  - Name it: Practical_7c_MouseKeyboard

Step 3: From the Activities panel, search "Click" and drag a 
        "Click" activity into the sequence.
  - Click "Indicate element on screen"
  - Click anywhere on the Notepad text area.
  - CursorMotionType: Instant (default)
  - This simulates a single LEFT click on Notepad.

Step 4: Drag a "Double Click" activity below.
  - Click "Indicate element on screen"
  - If you have any word typed in Notepad, indicate that word.
  - A double-click on a word selects it.
  - (Tip: First add a Type Into to type some text, then Double Click to select)

Step 5: Drag a "Hover" activity below.
  - Click "Indicate element on screen"
  - Hover over the Notepad Format menu (the word "Format" in the menu bar).
  - This simulates hovering — the menu will highlight but not open.

PART 2 - TYPE INTO

Step 6: Drag a "Type Into" activity.
  - Click "Indicate element on screen" → click the Notepad text area.
  - In the Text field, type: "This is typed by UiPath automation."
  - Run (F5) → watch UiPath type the sentence into Notepad automatically.

Step 7: In the Type Into Properties panel on the right:
  - SimulateType: True (this types instantly, not character by character)
  - EmptyField: True (this clears any existing text before typing)

PART 3 - TYPE SECURE TEXT

Step 8: Open a website that has a password field.
  - Open Chrome → go to: https://the-internet.herokuapp.com/login
  - Username: admin   Password: admin (it's a test website)

Step 9: In UiPath, drag a "Type Into" activity.
  - Indicate the Username field on the website.
  - Text: "admin"

Step 10: Drag a "Type Secure Text" activity.
  - Indicate the Password field on the website.
  - In the Password field: click the field → type the password 
    (UiPath will store it as a SecureString, hiding characters).
  - To input a hardcoded secure string:
    Use an Assign activity first:
      Left:  myPassword (type: SecureString)
      Right: New System.Net.NetworkCredential("","admin").SecurePassword
  - Then in Type Secure Text → Password: myPassword

Step 11: Run (F5).
  - Watch UiPath fill in the username and then the password (which will appear as dots).

================================================================
EXTRA NOTES FOR PRACTICAL 7:
================================================================
- "Attach Window" is essential when working with specific open windows.
  Always indicate the correct window, not just any part of the screen.
- "Find Element" is used to verify an element exists before interacting.
- "Find Children" lists all UI elements INSIDE a parent container.
- "Find Ancestor" finds the PARENT of a given element.
- "Type Into" types visible text. Use "SimulateType=True" for speed.
- "Type Secure Text" is for passwords — the text is never stored as plain string.
- Always use "Indicate element on screen" to point UiPath to the right UI element.
